## Step 3: Protein-Specific Annotation Guidelines (Final Checklist)

### Alpha-Helix (`class 0`)
- [x] Box tightly encloses the **entire helical ribbon** from start to end
- [x] Include the cylindrical tube — not just the axis
- [x] If two helices are connected by a loop, annotate each helix **separately**
- [x] Colour reference: **RED** ribbon in VMD Structure coloring

### Beta-Sheet (`class 1`)
- [x] Box encloses all **visible strands** of the sheet as one unit
- [x] Flat, arrow-like ribbons — typically **wider and shorter** than helices
- [x] If two separate sheets are visible, annotate each separately
- [x] Colour reference: **YELLOW** ribbon in VMD Structure coloring

### General Rules
- [x] No boxes on coil/loop regions (white ribbons in VMD) — only helix and sheet
- [x] Minimum bounding box: 15×15 px — skip sub-pixel fragments
- [x] Occluded structures: annotate if more than 50% is visible
- [x] Multiple structures per frame: ALL annotated, no omissions

